metadata.name: Entropes #80
metadata.description:
Entropes is an abstract generative art project consisting of patterns and textures made with a heuristic rectangle packing algorithm. It’s a blend of shapes, geometry and colour. It draws notable inspiration from the Bauhaus art style. All these attributes are fused to form aesthetics that create diversity while maintaining cohesiveness across this body of work.

_____________________________________________________________________________________

The details go down to the very last pixel and outputs can be saved right from the browser at a full resolution of 6400 x 9600 pixels which ensures the quality holds up across majority of displays and different print sizes.

_____________________________________________________________________________________

Programmed entirely using p5js.

_____________________________________________________________________________________

A project by Kamau Kamau and Ian Wright

metadata.name: Celestial Objects #57
metadata.description:
Celestial Objects is a generative collection imagining planets and stars in the space, with light and shadows being key themes. 

The artwork is primarily rendered using hundreds of thousands of points (more than a million in some cases) to create different aspects of the output including the sky textures, shooting stars and shadows on the planets. 

Celestial Objects is coded in p5.js, and please note that it takes 5-15 seconds for each output to render.

Controls (in live view): 
Press [2] to render 2000x2000px image
Press [4] to render 4000x4000px image
Press [s] to save the current view (default window size or 2000px or 4000px image)

metadata.name: Floating Point  #107
metadata.description:
'Floating Point' by pixelwank 

Inspired by pastel smudging and the aerial photography of Rich Caldwell, Floating Point has impressions of a landscape and other structures. 

Homage to floating point numbers and how just one decimal difference can change it all. 

Floating Point is also the fictional name of the place where this work takes me, where does it take you?

In live mode, click the image or press 's' or 'S' to save 3000x4000 png 

Thanks for collecting 
Shoutout Circolors for the support & frenship <3 

Made with p5js 
© pixelwank - CC BY 3.0, August 2022

metadata.name: Teppich #145
metadata.description:
The German term for rug, carpet, or tapestry; I’ve chosen this translation specifically because of its multiple meanings, what originally was a texture study of fabric became more recognizable as a rug. There are imperfections in the stitching, some bits of the underlay and adjacent colors bleeding into others. This name accurately captures both the intention and result of this piece.

Each Teppich can take anywhere from 15-60s to render depending on hardware. Please be patient and refer to your loading spinner for a taste.

Export to a 4500x3600 png with ’s’ for up to A3 printing or a jpg with ‘j’ for a smaller file size.

metadata.name: Florescentia #32
metadata.description:
Click Open then :
Press "s" to save a png
Press "p" to get a metal print of your Florescentia

Florescentia is a work that has gone through several stages. I started with a foundation, depicting a nebula in space with intricate details. As I let myself be guided by the code, I drew inspiration from artworks like "Meridian" by Matt DesLauries and "Anticyclone" by William Mapan. The freedom and fulfillment I experienced in the creative process inspired me to name it Florescentia.

metadata.name: Chaos #731
metadata.description:
Chaos seems to be the only constant thing in the universe. No matter the age, situation, location, success of any individual, from time to time, each one of us undergoes bouts of uncertainty. Chaos is something that is often portrayed in a negative light, but every once in a while it can end up being something beautiful as well. For example a nice surprise in an otherwise hectic day! 

This generative token is a celebration of chaos, a ray of hope amidst the tumultuous times that we live in, an escape from our internal vulnerabilities, a sense of closure and acceptance even when a lot might be going on in our lives. 

Feel free to mint as many as you want, gift it to your friends or loved ones, sell it, resell it or even make derivatives of your particular mint. I put in a reserve list for everybody who has collected any of my NFTs in the past so that my supporters don't miss out! This token is an expression of my gratitude to my supporters, and the entire FxHash community. Thank you all! 
Keep making art. No matter how hard today might be, be hopeful for a better tomorrow. 

Made with love in cables.gl

metadata.name: a multitude #60
metadata.description:
'a multitude' is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at NFT Show Europe, Valencia, 2022.

----------------------------------------------------------

a multitude of entities
a multitude of facts
a multitude of perspectives
a multitude

----------------------------------------------------------

In Live view

• When rendering is done, press 'S' or click the canvas to export a png.
By default, it renders at 2000x3000. To render at a width of W, add the URL parameter '?w=W'.
• Press 'F' to toggle full screen.
• Press 'C' to toggle cursor.

The artwork might look slightly different depending on browser & operating system.

Created by loackme
Coded in JavaScript, no libraries
